.docname {Table of contents}
.include {_Setup.qd}

A table of contents is a quick summary of the document where links to headings are displayed in a visual hierarchy.

- `paged` and `slides` documents also display the corresponding page number.
- `slides` documents constrain the maximum height, making the table of contents vertically scrollable.

You can display a table of contents through the **`.tableofcontents`** function, with the following optional parameters:

| Parameter | Description | Accepts | Default |
|-----------|-------------|---------|---------|
| `title` | Title that precedes the table of contents. If unset, it is automatically localized. | Inline content | Automatically localized if [`.doclang`](Document-metadata.qd)'s locale is supported (e.g., `Table of Contents` for English) |
| `maxdepth` | Maximum level of headings to display. For example, `maxdepth = 2` collects `# This` and `## This`, but not `### This`. | `Integer` | `3` |
| `focus` | If set, adds focus to the item with the same text as this argument. Inline style (strong, emphasis, etc.) is ignored when comparing the text content. | [Inline content](Markdown-content.qd#inline-content) | (none) |

```markdown
.tableofcontents maxdepth:{2}

## A

...

### A.A

...

### A.B

...

## B

...

## C

### C.A

#### C.A.A

...
```

